# AWS Infrastructure Deployment via Mixed Local and Registry Terraform Modules

This project demonstrates an infrastructure-as-code pattern that combines **custom local child modules** with **community-vetted modules from the public Terraform Registry**. This specific update parameterizes the public S3 bucket module by passing input configurations directly from a root-level variable file.

---

## Project Directory Architecture

The repository layout includes the root configuration files along with an isolated directory containing internal compute logic:

```text
.
├── main.tf                            # Root module: Instantiates registry S3 and local EC2 modules
├── provide.tf                         # Root module: Configures the target AWS region
├── terra.tf                           # Root module: Defines provider versions and constraints
├── variable.tf                        # Root module: Manages global inputs (e.g., S3 bucket naming)
├── terraform.tfstate                  # Local active deployment state file
├── terraform.tfstate.backup           # Last known good state backup
└── own-terra-child-module-details    # Internal directory for custom module code
    └── ec2-own                        # Custom child module for compute provisioning
        ├── data.tf                    # Dynamic Ubuntu AMI data source query
        └── main.tf                    # EC2 resource definitions and local variable blocks

```

