## Technical Task Roadmap & Implementations

### Task 1: Main Execution Core, Variables & Version Constraints (Root Module)

The root workspace handles provider locking, global variable parameters, and block coordination. The registry S3 module now dynamically references a root variable rather than using a hardcoded string.

#### `terra.tf`

Enforces strict provider rules. The AWS provider constraint is set to `>= 6.42.0` to support upstream registry requirements and avoid engine compilation lockups.

```hcl
terraform {
  required_providers {
    aws = {
      source  = "hashicorp/aws"
      version = ">= 6.42.0"  # Configured to meet upstream module prerequisites
    }
    random = {
      source  = "hashicorp/random"
      version = "3.8.1"
    }
  }
}

```

#### `provide.tf`

Establishes default context arguments for the primary infrastructure plane.

```hcl
# Configure the default AWS Provider to target the Mumbai region
provider "aws" {
  region = "ap-south-1"
}

```

#### `variable.tf`

Declares global input variables used to pass configurations dynamically into individual modules.

```hcl
variable "buk-name" {
  type    = string
  default = "my-bucket-from-variable-use"
}

```

#### `main.tf`

Implements the call blocks. The public S3 bucket names are mapped to the variable defined above.

```hcl
# Deprecated local module invocation - retained for architectural history tracking
#module "eco-s3" {
#  source = "./own-terra-child-module-details/s3-own"
#}

# Task 1a: Consume verified external modules from the public registry using root variables
module "s3-bucket" {                                                 #Imported module
  source  = "terraform-aws-modules/s3-bucket/aws"
  version = "5.14.0"

  bucket = var.buk-name                                             #variable name
}

# Task 1b: Consume unmanaged custom modules via local pathing references
module "eco-ec2" {
  source = "./own-terra-child-module-details/ec2-own"
}

```

